snippet: His association with the Internet firm Waywire had become an embarrassment for Mayor Cory A. Booker of Newark even as he seemed poised to capture a Senate seat in a special election.
abstract: Newark Mayor Cory A Booker is cutting all ties to Waywire, Internet start-up that he founded with money from well-connected figures in Silicon Valley and elsewhere; association and attendant criticism have become embarrassment for Booker as he seeks Democratic nomination for United States Senate in New Jersey.
lead_paragraph: His association with the Internet firm Waywire had become an embarrassment for Mayor Cory A. Booker of Newark even as he seemed poised to capture a Senate seat in a special election.

headline.main: Booker to End Association With Start-Up He Founded
headline.print_headline: Booker to End Association With Start-Up He Founded
